Burkina Faso Soldiers Fire Shots in Air at Military Base, Extending Unrest

-- B y   S i m o n   G o n g o
-- 
2011-05-30T10:45:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/burkina-faso-soldiers-fire-shots-in-air-at-military-base-extending-unrest.html
Soldiers in Burkina Faso, which has
seen four months of civil and military unrest, fired shots in
the air yesterday at Kaya base, 100 kilometers (62 miles) from
the capital, Ouagadougou, said resident Rosine Koala.  “They began shooting at about 9 p.m.,” she said by phone
today. “They fired for two or three hours.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simon Gongo in Ouagadougou at 
 sgongo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
